		<!-- message -->
		<div>I posted about this a while ago. Nobody ever noticed it?<br />
(In my oppinion only)<br />
there is an Aggro limit. its very real and easy to  see.<br />
<br />
before the aoe taunt came around remeber tank switching?<br />
<br />
tanks beats the hell out of mob procing like mad  and 2.5 min later you try to taunt it off.. you really think you failed taunt 10 times?<br />
<br />
No the warrior was at the max taunt limit. and he had to turn off attack to lose aggro. Took another 62+ warrior a good 45 sec of taunting and procing to peel doomshade off of me (i know i know.. but thats the best place to practice it for later) without me attacking.<br />
<br />
hate also seems to be a decaying value. So when you finally taunted that mob off that cleric it was becasue his aggro had faded. 1 hit was all i took to get him back on top.<br />
<br />
we have all seen this.. slow resisted 4-5 times and no taunting will get you on top of the list if he continues to cast. Hell aoe taunt even fails somtimes but i thinks thats more of a bug.<br />
<br />
If there is a hard capped number, say 10,000 (probably more but lets say it is this)  and you taunt you get top of aggro list +1 making it 10,001. as the top of aggro is capped at 10,000 a taunt making you 10001 fails. This includes aoe taunt if the memwipe fails (assuming it reduces others hate or somthing along that line)<br />
<br />
low hp aggro must be 10,000 hate as well. Seeing as people said that sometimes low hp aggro is not absolute.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
