			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>more agro test</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#131619" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>These tests were done some months ago and I no longer have the logs, but here is the summary of results.<br />
<br />
At the time of these test, Farlander was 65th level I believe as was I.  I am a ranger btw, Farlander is a warrior, and Samanthea was a 60 something cleric.  We went to FG because the shrooms respond.<br />
<br />
I do not recall seeing any of the 4 succesful taunt behavior in order to get agro during these two tests, and the others we did relating to archery agro.<br />
<br />
Anyway here's the tests.<br />
-------------------------------------<br />
Objective:<br />
Attempt to determine if taunt only puts you on the top of the hate list, or it adds additional agro besides that of moving you to the top of the hate list.<br />
<br />
Test 1:<br />
Process:<br />
I snare a mushroom 20 times. 10 tangling weeds, 10 snares.<br />
Farlander to taunt until the mushroom responds, that way we can determine the difference in behavior if taunt fails<br />
<br />
Result:<br />
I snared 10 shots of tangling weeds, and 10 shots of ensnare, Samanthea kept me healed with some HoTs to try and remove her agro from the test.<br />
<br />
Farlander taunted once after I was finished snaring, the Mushroom responded to the taunt, and Farlander got agro.<br />
<br />
Test 2:<br />
Process:<br />
Farlander will taunt 20 times, then I will snare.<br />
<br />
Result:<br />
Farlander had to go defensive so he could get off 25 taunt attempts, on 14 taunts the Mushroom responded so we assumed that meant 14 taunts worked.<br />
<br />
I snared and had agro.<br />
<br />
---------------------------------</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
