		<!-- message -->
		<div>It may be worthwhile to bring a SK friend along and have him cast a ceritain amount of their +pure agro spells on the mob and then the warrior trying to taunt it off. For example<br />
<br />
<br />
Sk casts 1 agro spell, warrior taunts untill he gets agro (both of them not meleeing or doing anything else). Do it a few times and see how many taunts it takes.<br />
<br />
Then the SK casts the same spell 2 times, warrior taunts untill he gets agro (both of them not meleeing or doing anything else). Do it a few times and see how many taunts it takes.<br />
<br />
This could figure out what the maximum taunt cap is (if there is infact one) because if you don't get agro right after one sucessful taunt (read:if the mob gives a message, although the messages may be broken) then you have reached the cap.<br />
<br />
/shrug<br />
<br />
Interesting tests folks, maybe if I have a SK friend log in tonight I can try this out.</div>
