		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				 As you can see, after 63 successful taunts, 1 CH pulled the mob right off of me. This shows pretty clearly that taunt is not a fixed aggro value and if it adds any amount of aggro it is insignifigant.<br />

			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div><br />
<br />
<br />
I wouldn't say this is necessarily true.  It's long been determined that taunt does nothing if you already hold aggro on the mob.  There may be code such that if you don't have agro, a taunt adds hate, but if you do than it adds nothing.  So it's possible your first taunt had a fixed aggro value that put you at the top of the hate list, and once there your next 62 taunts add no more value because the mob was already on you.</div>
